cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and neural models, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses weight sharing in neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper incorporates prior knowledge into neural models, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with text categorization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses improved performance, which is a common goal in neural networks and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
